07633nam a22010335i 9789048513369DE-B159720210927121507.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210927t20122011ne     fo  d z      eng d  a2011417647  a97890485133697 a10.1515/97890485133692doi  a(DE-B1597)517622  a(OCoLC)1083629205  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anecNL00aJC423b.H7533 2011 7aPOL0000002bisacsh04a321.800aHow Democracy Works :bPolitical Representation and Policy Congruence in Modern Societies /ced. by Martin Rosema, Kees Aarts, Bas Denters. 1aAmsterdam : bAmsterdam University Press, c[2012] 4c©2011  a1 online resource (293 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tPreface -- t1. How Democracy Works: An Introduction -- tPart I. The Basic Principles: Political Representation and Policy Congruence -- t2. The Dynamics of Political Representation -- t3. Approaching Perfect Policy Congruence: Measurement, Development, and Relevance for Political Representation -- t4. Dynamic Representation from Above -- t5. Is Governing Becoming more Contentious? -- tPart II. The Citizen Perspective -- t6. Democratic Congruence Re-Established: The Perspective of 'Substantive' Democracy -- t7. Does Democratic Satisfaction Reflect Regime Performance? -- t8. Citizens' Views about Good Local Governance -- t9. Patterns of Party Evaluations -- tPart III. Political Representation in the European Union -- t10. The Electoral Consequences of Low Turnout in European Parliament Elections -- t11. Assessing the Quality of European Democracy: Are Voters Voting Correctly? -- tPart IV. The Impact of the Economic Context -- t12. The Impact of the Economic Crisis in Europe: "I'm doing fine" -- t13. The Changing Macro Context of Norwegian Voters: From Center- Periphery Cleavages to Oil Wealth -- tList of Contributors -- tAppendix: Publications by Jacques Thomassen -- tReferences0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn this book, a group of leading scholars analyzes the functioning of modern democracies by focusing on two basic principles: political representation and policy congruence. Drawing on recent survey data from a variety of national and international research projects, they demonstrate how political representation works and mostly leads to a fair degree of policy congruence between citizens and their representatives. They also present new insights on the sources of satisfaction with democracy and the impact of the economy on elections and political trust. This book is published on the occasion of the retirement of Jacques Thomassen as distinguished professor of political science at the University of Twente. The contributors include Russell Dalton, Hans‐Dieter Klingemann, Pippa Norris, Ola Listhaug, Hanne Marthe Narud, Jan van Deth, Peter Mair, Cees van der Eijk, Hermann Schmitt, Sören Holmberg and Rudy Andeweg. Martin Rosema, Bas Denters and Kees Aarts are affiliated with the Centre for the Study of Democracy (CSD) and the Institute for Innovation and Governance Studies (IGS) at the University of Twente.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aDemocracy. 0aRepresentative government and representation. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAardal, Bernt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAarts, Kees, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAarts, Kees, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAndeweg, Rudy B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDalton, Russell J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDenters, Bas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDenters, Bas, eeditor.4e